article.headline: TCU 62, North Texas 58
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Chudi Chinweze scored 18 points, including the go-ahead basket with 4:13 remaining, as TCU beat North Texas 62-58 Saturday night. Corey Santee added 12 points and six rebounds, and Marcus Shropshire had 11 points for TCU (2-5) in a back-and-forth game that was tied 15 times. Jerome Rogers scored 15 points to lead North Texas (3-2). Leonard Hopkins added 11 points, although he did it on 3-of-16 shooting. Will Smith had eight points and seven rebounds for UNT. TCU led 28-27 after a sloppy first half. The Horned Frogs shot 29 percent in the half (8-of-28) while UNT was just 30 percent (9-of-30). The teams also combined for more turnovers (24) than field goals (17) in the half. But the Horned Frogs improved in the second half, shooting 42 percent to UNT's 31 percent.
